# View Pattern

View state lives in the URL: `?view=auth|app|llm&sub=...`.

- Use `parseViewState(viewParam, subParam, defaultView)` from `@/lib/view-router` to read.
- Use `buildViewUrl(view, sub)` + `router.push()` (or `router.replace()`) to navigate.
- Never store the current view in React state.
- `defaultView` = `"auth"` when no user, `"app"` when authenticated.
- `useSearchParams` MUST be wrapped in a `<Suspense>` boundary (Next.js 16 prerender requirement).

Valid subs:
- `auth`: `login` | `register` | `forgot-password`
- `app`: `dashboard` | `sessions` | `monitoring` | `settings`
- `llm`: `model-loader` | `chat` | `event-submit`
